<subSubSection id="34704CEB640AA12554007499013118A2" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="notes">
<paragraph id="820E28553DA08658D74D13E996857513" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BBC812A4AF4D50FA34AFF8D28DDC39FA" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
Described from 
<normalizedToken id="A8881ECB53BF65682D5FD4A621055531" originalValue="páramos">paramos</normalizedToken>
of Costa Rica, and mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation id="DAE30025326C1E6477C519880D6EC46C" author="Pohl, RW" editor="Davidse, G" journalOrPublisher="Alismataceae a Cyperaceae. Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Mexico" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="237 - 240" refId="B28" refString="Pohl, RW, Davidse, G, 1994. 46. Agrostis L. In: Davidse, G, Sousa, M, Sanchez, MS, Chater, AO, Eds., Flora Mesoamericana (Vol 6). Alismataceae a Cyperaceae. Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Mexico: 237 - 240" title="46. Agrostis L." volumeTitle="Flora Mesoamericana (Vol 6)." year="1994">Pohl and Davidse (1994)</bibRefCitation>
to also occur in alpine pastures of Guatemala and Mexico, 
<taxonomicName id="836DB89A8D364FC4E63C21214493B07F" genus="A." lsidName="A. turrialbae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="turrialbae">
<emphasis id="7D5CDD303645854C9A858A9A2951623A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. turrialbae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has also been included in checklists for Colombia (
<bibRefCitation id="9094AB592C0F083C21C8E8FE37414057" author="Giraldo-Canas, D" editor="Bernal, R" journalOrPublisher="2). Instituto de Ciencias Naturales, Universidad Nacional de Colombia, Bogota D. C." pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="2127 - 2205" refId="B10" refString="Giraldo-Canas, D, Londono, X, Clark, LG, 2016. Poaceae. In: Bernal, R, Gradstein, SR, Celis, M, Eds., Catalogo de plantas y liquenes de Colombia (Vol. 2). Instituto de Ciencias Naturales, Universidad Nacional de Colombia, Bogota D.C.: 2127 - 2205" title="Poaceae." volumeTitle="Catalogo de plantas y liquenes de Colombia (Vol." year="2016">
<normalizedToken id="D99C3012A98FE786C4FE5AC2D80F270C" originalValue="Giraldo-Cañas">Giraldo-Canas</normalizedToken>
et al. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
) and Venezuela (
<bibRefCitation id="D6D06A095E12F05ED5287FA158E61293" author="Hokche, O" journalOrPublisher="Fundacion Instituto Botanico de Venezuela, Caracas" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" refId="B16" refString="Hokche, O, Berry, PE, Huber, O [Eds], 2008. Nuevo Catalogo de la Flora Vascular de Venezuela. Fundacion Instituto Botanico de Venezuela, Caracas" title="Nuevo Catalogo de la Flora Vascular de Venezuela." year="2008">Hokche et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
). However, there is a lack of consensus on the identity of 
<taxonomicName id="D2A78990BC4D865AE3509C4D13C5B137" genus="A." lsidName="A. turrialbae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="turrialbae">
<emphasis id="4F78C85906A6C1978715BF4FE9DF1DF8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. turrialbae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and how to differentiate it from 
<taxonomicName id="CA22BE763E9F731D20159E9B727EC058" genus="A." lsidName="A. perennans" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="perennans">
<emphasis id="0A765FB423B09FC362994064A4215EAF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. perennans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.l., with all type material of 
<taxonomicName id="F2D86841A2A6A93512E7CD21AE25D379" genus="A." lsidName="A. turrialbae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="turrialbae">
<emphasis id="2F9E8F276698C3660E691E62C6E15E5E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. turrialbae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and its synonyms out on loan at the time of writing this publication to help clarify this. The principal discrepancy refers to the form of the leaf blades, with the protologue and 
<bibRefCitation id="5014FA5D3BD03222757E2FE99B116F96" author="Pohl, RW" editor="Burger, WC" journalOrPublisher="Fieldiana Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="1 - 608" refId="B27" refString="Pohl, RW, 1980. Family 15. Gramineae. In: Burger, WC, Ed., Flora Costaricensis. Fieldiana Botany 4: 1 - 608" title="Family 15. Gramineae." volume="4" volumeTitle="Flora Costaricensis." year="1980">Pohl (1980)</bibRefCitation>
mentioning filiform flat or folded leaf blades, while 
<bibRefCitation id="D363BD3B1F73707558FB0A1EDA8328D1" author="Pohl, RW" editor="Davidse, G" journalOrPublisher="Alismataceae a Cyperaceae. Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Mexico" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="237 - 240" refId="B28" refString="Pohl, RW, Davidse, G, 1994. 46. Agrostis L. In: Davidse, G, Sousa, M, Sanchez, MS, Chater, AO, Eds., Flora Mesoamericana (Vol 6). Alismataceae a Cyperaceae. Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Mexico: 237 - 240" title="46. Agrostis L." volumeTitle="Flora Mesoamericana (Vol 6)." year="1994">Pohl and Davidse (1994)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="B938C3A56131C4AB6670ACFB9DE85BA9" author="Morales-Quiros, JF" editor="Hammel, BE" journalOrPublisher="Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden 93 (3)" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="598 - 821" refId="B22" refString="Morales-Quiros, JF, 2003. Poaceae. In: Hammel, BE, Grayum, MH, Herrera-Mora, C, Zamora-Villalobos, N, Eds., Manual of Plants of Costa Rica. Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden 93(3): 598 - 821" title="Poaceae." volumeTitle="Manual of Plants of Costa Rica." year="2003">
<normalizedToken id="78FBD54A52F41655D6BAF47FBD0B7CCB" originalValue="Morales-Quirós">Morales-Quiros</normalizedToken>
(2003)
</bibRefCitation>
state the blades to be involute and narrow, 0.2-1 mm in diameter as rolled, and rarely the cauline leaf blades being flat, and use this character to differentiate it from the usually flat bladed 
<taxonomicName id="FEED9249DFD4EBD2B1F7C99DCE975615" genus="A." lsidName="A. perennans" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="perennans">
<emphasis id="92E5DDBC0F7A23863DDBA7A47162A096" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. perennans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This may relate to the species 
<taxonomicName id="0545ECCF6E87834A304DA672D7D7711F" genus="A." lsidName="A. arcta" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="arcta">
<emphasis id="2C4E5026D34E6332DF341D0A4E341CF5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. arcta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="074FB9704B9E9C0C5385BCF9422E1ADB" genus="A." lsidName="A. vesca" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="vesca">
<emphasis id="2270F7400A54078E2621EB672EA1C117" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. vesca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, described from Guatemala and considered synonyms of 
<taxonomicName id="1A69D2EE63FACD061A6381A56375BCAD" genus="A." lsidName="A. turrialbae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="turrialbae">
<emphasis id="0ECD5AAEF0517757FF9AEE7AD7505732" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. turrialbae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="4FC7E2A2B6AF3206DDE3122529712FC0" author="Pohl, RW" editor="Davidse, G" journalOrPublisher="Alismataceae a Cyperaceae. Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Mexico" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="237 - 240" refId="B28" refString="Pohl, RW, Davidse, G, 1994. 46. Agrostis L. In: Davidse, G, Sousa, M, Sanchez, MS, Chater, AO, Eds., Flora Mesoamericana (Vol 6). Alismataceae a Cyperaceae. Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Mexico: 237 - 240" title="46. Agrostis L." volumeTitle="Flora Mesoamericana (Vol 6)." year="1994">Pohl and Davidse (1994)</bibRefCitation>
, with the protologues mentioning leaf blades being firm, folded and involute, curved, in 
<taxonomicName id="7D1E3CB73358B31A2B536A4DDFD8BA24" genus="A." lsidName="A. arcta" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="arcta">
<emphasis id="CC2A6DFFC80E684945991619FA86188C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. arcta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, or flat, filiform, or involute and straight in 
<emphasis id="1A77E4EF1F41A7C67EFBE56F36BD4760" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
<taxonomicName id="1AE0AF9ED1872D24CB78C62AEAF5803E" genus="A." lsidName="A. vesca" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="vesca">A. vesca</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="DC97A04D744DBF0501B22D84A879EC5B" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Agrostis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Agrostis perennans" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="perennans">Agrostis perennans</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, in its broad sense, can also have involute or filiform leaf blades based on species currently considered synonyms of 
<taxonomicName id="1D409C99DAA551E1436CF5439A9C1D50" genus="A." lsidName="A. perennans" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="perennans">
<emphasis id="CA7F8B89B545C14F188F2E7009B2394B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. perennans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, e.g. 
<taxonomicName id="E5AC0CE56CD5D0411E8DEFEB55148013" genus="A." lsidName="A. aberrans" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="aberrans">
<emphasis id="3DDFCA0600600FD22EBA0F77D10BB9A0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. aberrans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Steud., 
<taxonomicName id="F9AA9A8823E336D2FD67CD5DC8541CCD" genus="A." lsidName="A. kufium" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="kufium">
<emphasis id="A38CBBC089F0DE66E68995F81AB20E8F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. kufium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Speg., 
<taxonomicName id="565BB3E797EBFCF9AADD3F7DE86BE861" genus="A." lsidName="A. tenuifolia subsp. var. var. fretensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="variety" species="tenuifolia" subSpecies="var." variety="fretensis">A. tenuifolia M. Bieb. var. fretensis</taxonomicName>
Hook. f., 
<taxonomicName id="DDF4FD083C9A4019BFB9CD9BD175034B" authority="P.Beauv., 1812" authorityName="Kunth" authorityYear="1816" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Vilfa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Vilfa elegans" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis id="3C6C74D1DCDD7F2C70123BACF5BBA4FE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Vilfa elegans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="10163E16D0F71D542CF25EA4BEDD225B" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
While all literature (
<bibRefCitation id="421747B63AD8D15C247F028BD57F0093" author="Pohl, RW" editor="Burger, WC" journalOrPublisher="Fieldiana Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="1 - 608" refId="B27" refString="Pohl, RW, 1980. Family 15. Gramineae. In: Burger, WC, Ed., Flora Costaricensis. Fieldiana Botany 4: 1 - 608" title="Family 15. Gramineae." volume="4" volumeTitle="Flora Costaricensis." year="1980">Pohl 1980</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="F50EBF01001A170034210512E926B86C" author="Pohl, RW" editor="Davidse, G" journalOrPublisher="Alismataceae a Cyperaceae. Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Mexico" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="237 - 240" refId="B28" refString="Pohl, RW, Davidse, G, 1994. 46. Agrostis L. In: Davidse, G, Sousa, M, Sanchez, MS, Chater, AO, Eds., Flora Mesoamericana (Vol 6). Alismataceae a Cyperaceae. Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Mexico: 237 - 240" title="46. Agrostis L." volumeTitle="Flora Mesoamericana (Vol 6)." year="1994">Pohl and Davidse 1994</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="4400CD44A19A2C5A6017BAB699825053" author="Morales-Quiros, JF" editor="Hammel, BE" journalOrPublisher="Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden 93 (3)" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="598 - 821" refId="B22" refString="Morales-Quiros, JF, 2003. Poaceae. In: Hammel, BE, Grayum, MH, Herrera-Mora, C, Zamora-Villalobos, N, Eds., Manual of Plants of Costa Rica. Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden 93(3): 598 - 821" title="Poaceae." volumeTitle="Manual of Plants of Costa Rica." year="2003">
<normalizedToken id="0EC09EDE4AAC7C1E59EE17F5866B9D9C" originalValue="Morales-Quirós">Morales-Quiros</normalizedToken>
2003
</bibRefCitation>
) also differentiates 
<taxonomicName id="35F77A907791F08B4242F807B8C7A096" genus="A." lsidName="A. perennans" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="perennans">
<emphasis id="DD3AD67D9720DB28FAD4C70BD16F957C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. perennans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="760C6A41B998F6042EA5147D33998FDA" genus="A." lsidName="A. turrialbae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="turrialbae">
<emphasis id="A9B8756FAEE9083FCE95B2E959CB34B7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. turrialbae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by stating there is a lack of conspicuous basal foliage in the former, this may not be a good differentiating character as 
<taxonomicName id="7A381A664F987183A859ADBD68F8F862" genus="A." lsidName="A. perennans" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="perennans">
<emphasis id="689A56812BEE08CC209C4B3B5EA7BB38" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. perennans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
usually has blades concentrated at the base of the plant when it is young, and only in subsequent flowering seasons it begins to elongate and lose its basal foliage. 
<bibRefCitation id="DD6D2F642674D690734E4E8159DABF95" author="Pohl, RW" editor="Burger, WC" journalOrPublisher="Fieldiana Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="1 - 608" refId="B27" refString="Pohl, RW, 1980. Family 15. Gramineae. In: Burger, WC, Ed., Flora Costaricensis. Fieldiana Botany 4: 1 - 608" title="Family 15. Gramineae." volume="4" volumeTitle="Flora Costaricensis." year="1980">Pohl (1980)</bibRefCitation>
also mentions that paleas are minute in 
<taxonomicName id="51673926D6767369C158BB3F9B1144F1" genus="A." lsidName="A. perennans" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="perennans">
<emphasis id="B15A46B932F9105D39D1BAC1159E518E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. perennans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while in 
<taxonomicName id="9133E635090B4CD4036DCA6BB2B9C807" genus="A." lsidName="A. turrialbae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="turrialbae">
<emphasis id="EDDFC93943BD28BC9CF3327A680224F3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. turrialbae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
paleas are absent, but this character appears to be too variable to be useful. Discrepancy in spikelet size is also apparent, with the 
<taxonomicName id="07AE8A3C92AE5A49D6669BD3082B7F3A" genus="A." lsidName="A. turrialbae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="turrialbae">
<emphasis id="83565D561D6369D6DFC8979701544834" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. turrialbae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
protologue stating 1.75 mm long and the 
<taxonomicName id="F0BB168A80E167EFF9CD52E9D8161D48" genus="A." lsidName="A. vesca" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="vesca">
<emphasis id="94FE401A04CC3128CA3131519F840BDB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. vesca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
protologue stating 1.6-1.8 mm long, while all other publications describing the species (
<bibRefCitation id="155D2D556F1B04B204987136F045DF36" author="Pohl, RW" editor="Burger, WC" journalOrPublisher="Fieldiana Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="1 - 608" refId="B27" refString="Pohl, RW, 1980. Family 15. Gramineae. In: Burger, WC, Ed., Flora Costaricensis. Fieldiana Botany 4: 1 - 608" title="Family 15. Gramineae." volume="4" volumeTitle="Flora Costaricensis." year="1980">Pohl 1980</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="E20C34016208F1C6648620EB390F89F0" author="Pohl, RW" editor="Davidse, G" journalOrPublisher="Alismataceae a Cyperaceae. Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Mexico" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="237 - 240" refId="B28" refString="Pohl, RW, Davidse, G, 1994. 46. Agrostis L. In: Davidse, G, Sousa, M, Sanchez, MS, Chater, AO, Eds., Flora Mesoamericana (Vol 6). Alismataceae a Cyperaceae. Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Mexico: 237 - 240" title="46. Agrostis L." volumeTitle="Flora Mesoamericana (Vol 6)." year="1994">Pohl and Davidse 1994</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="062ABAD0E0ABC63B7131C5CA792E6F41" author="Morales-Quiros, JF" editor="Hammel, BE" journalOrPublisher="Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden 93 (3)" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="598 - 821" refId="B22" refString="Morales-Quiros, JF, 2003. Poaceae. In: Hammel, BE, Grayum, MH, Herrera-Mora, C, Zamora-Villalobos, N, Eds., Manual of Plants of Costa Rica. Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden 93(3): 598 - 821" title="Poaceae." volumeTitle="Manual of Plants of Costa Rica." year="2003">
<normalizedToken id="D555AA508486D5C8F166D111115BCC82" originalValue="Morales-Quirós">Morales-Quiros</normalizedToken>
2003
</bibRefCitation>
) state 2-2.1 mm or 2-2.8 mm long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="622F3E6BAF0882AFE77029AB657E2536" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
We here tentatively differentiate the two species by 
<taxonomicName id="BBF778863F8E301C30C626F155DAFC0B" genus="A." lsidName="A. turrialbae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="turrialbae">
<emphasis id="F6CF39C1A196B22C7FA105EE0D07E931" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. turrialbae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
having leaf blades filiform, 0.2-1 mm wide when opened out, thin and flaccid, leaves mainly basal at maturity, and plants generally smaller with culms to 40 cm tall and panicles to 12 cm long and 6 cm wide (vs. leaf blades flat or conduplicate, (1-)1.5-6 mm wide when opened out, rarely involute in the basal leaves, usually thickened at the margins and keel, firm, leaves mainly basal early in the flowering season but tending to become mostly cauline with maturity, and plants generally larger, with culms to 100 cm tall and panicles often larger, to 22 cm long and 11 cm wide in 
<taxonomicName id="6B47996A5101E90E690424F4F0A428A9" genus="A." lsidName="A. perennans" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="perennans">
<emphasis id="0D160A35EA8B93489CDD1B0B2004162B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. perennans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.l.). No specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="FC0E1ACFE83986FE35E975D7AF4C0727" genus="A." lsidName="A. turrialbae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="turrialbae">
<emphasis id="1FF3E7C6F32E76E4987B45D1B2371AD7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. turrialbae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that fit this delineation have been found at US from either Colombia or Venezuela. Furthermore, 
<taxonomicName id="7D76FC19167BF40EED44D877B0A0AA4C" genus="A." lsidName="A. turrialbae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="turrialbae">
<emphasis id="AEAF30F9AA7FAF47B3FD9EFE2268EC11" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. turrialbae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be better included among the broad 
<taxonomicName id="3697E1538A95BA9881FA85AEEAA0AE61" genus="A." lsidName="A. perennans" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="perennans">
<emphasis id="E4B4A7E64929C55FA1E68995C5272BBA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. perennans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex until a satisfactory revision can be done of this species complex, which has been found to comprise evolutionarily distinct lineages in unpublished molecular phylogenies (Konstantin Romaschenko, pers. communication).
</paragraph>
